          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is an adaptation of a well known Hindu story originally derived from the Mahābhārata about an encounter between the epic hero Arjuna and the deity Śiva in his form as the Hunter or Mountain Man called Kirāta. Manuscript contains only the first and second of a total 18 sections (sarga) of the poem.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kirātārjunīya</title>
              <title type="vernacular">किरातार्जुनीय</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Bhāravi</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: itī śrī kurātārjunīye mahākāvye lakṣmyaṃke bhāravikṛtau vyāsāgamano nāmadvitīyaḥ sargaḥ (Part 2, f. 7v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
